t need to add a dependency since Spring 7 is new.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing JUnit compatibility**\\n\\nI’m noting that there could be an issue with `org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ClassTemplateInvocationContextProvider`, which isn’t included in older versions. The build cache is at 6.0.3, so that's good. However, I’m concerned that if the top-level test class is annotated with @ClassTemplate and that component is missing, it might not run properly in JUnit 5. I also want to ensure that line lengths are okay, as that might help avoid any formatting issues.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_GJ6vkth98zcxU5U6nnCgxg2N|fc_0f01b53f83e9979b016a287d8cb4dc8195ab95f9620707dd34", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "awk 'length($0)>120 {print FNR \":\" length($0) \":\" $0}' tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/TestClassScannerTest.java && find tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test -maxdepth 1 -name 'TestClassScannerTest.java' -print"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 633, "output": 1214, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50999, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781038438711, "responseId": "resp_0f01b53f83e9979b016a287d6775bc819595bfc57f8e60dfe7"}}
